Sat Jul 18 18:30:18 UTC 2026 - Martin Pluskal <mpluskal@suse.com>

- Update to version 1.19.29:
  * Add JLS (TLS obfuscation) support across many outbounds and
    listeners (anytls, vmess/vless/trojan, shadowsocks, snell) and
    align its handshake handling with JLS v3
  * Add ReSTLS and ShadowTLS support for anytls, snell and the
    vmess/vless/trojan proxies; reimplement ShadowTLS and make its
    v2/v3 read deadlines recoverable
  * Add a ShadowQUIC outbound and listener with JLS pre-flight
    fallback handling
  * Improve OpenVPN: TLS rekey and data-ciphers negotiation,
    tls-crypt-v2 and TLSAuth support, reconnect on server soft
    reset (#2989, #2978, #2969)
  * Sync anytls to v0.0.13 and fix anytls listener config parsing
  * Add name-cert-verify and per-provider override-expr options
  * Fix DNS and rule handling: full-width IP-SUFFIX panic, CNAME
    query matching a hosts domain-entry and DOMAIN-WILDCARD
    ignoring the sniffed hostname (#2975, #2965, #2956)
  * Fix wireguard per-peer reserved, a TUIC stream leak, a reaper
    goroutine busy-loop and listener duplicate-name checks
    (#2958, #2959, #2964, #2948)

-------------------------------------------------------------------
Wed Jul  8 07:20:39 UTC 2026 - Martin Pluskal <mpluskal@suse.com>

- Update to version 1.19.28:
  * Restore the original Clash /proxies REST API behaviour
    (behaviour change for API consumers)
  * Add new outbound and protocol support: rematch outbound with
    REMATCH-NAME rules, MKCP and TLS-mirror for VMess, shadow-TLS
    for Snell, ReSTLS for the Shadowsocks listener and h3-l4proxy
    for the masque outbound
  * Add DNS fallback-lazy-query and listen-routing-mark options
  * Add routing-mark support for listeners and DNS plus a
    top-level external-controller-routing-mark option
  * Fix several crashes and panics (AmneziaWG slice bounds,
    masque dial failures, sing-mux UDP writes, TUIC v5 UDP relay
    and a nil-slice rand.IntN)
  * Bundle the vendored crypto/tls fix for CVE-2026-42505
- Restrict tar_scm tag matching to release tags (match-tag v*)
  so the version resolves correctly now that upstream also places
  a rolling Prerelease-Alpha tag on the release commit

